        <p><p class="first_letter">A</p>lexa Fairchild was born on X. She lived and died in a different era from our own. An era before every bit regarding every body was archived and made unalterable.</p>


        <p>Before mystery became a near impossibility.</p>

        <p>What we know comes from an entry in the old Wiki database, last dated X along with a few supplemental documents that showed up in various datamines discovered over the years. All this information had been gathered and placed at the decrypted [address].</p>

        <p>We know she was born in St. Paul, Minnesota. She attended a small liberal arts college Bryn Mawr and then Harvard, where she earned a PhD in theoretical physics. She won various awards.</p>

        <p>Her wiki-entry makes no mention of her disappearance, presumably it occurred after the final updates to the file system. </p>

        <p>In X, Fairchild was profiled in Time magazine's List of 100. It gives by far the richest characterization of her of anything we have.</p>


